      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;flatfile-agential-resource-system-specification&#34;&gt;flatfile-agential-resource-system-specification&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;what-this-is&#34;&gt;What this is&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This spec describes how a &lt;a href=&#34;../specification/specification.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;Specification&lt;/a&gt; is encoded and stored in the Flatfile Agential Resource System.&#xA;In FARS, a Specification is a markdown &lt;a href=&#34;../resource.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;Resource&lt;/a&gt; file living in the &lt;code&gt;spec/&lt;/code&gt; locale.&#xA;It carries YAML frontmatter that identifies the concept being specified and declares the predicates that apply to it.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;file-layout&#34;&gt;File layout&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Simple specifications with no colocated files live at &lt;code&gt;spec/{id}.md&lt;/code&gt;.&#xA;A specification with colocated skills, runbooks, or scripts MUST live in a subdirectory:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
